## Typography

Brand Font:
Bebas Neue

UI Heading Font:
Outfit

Body Font:
Inter

Rules:

Typography Hierarchy

Brand Font (Bebas Neue)

Use only for:

- Logo
- Hero banners
- Marketing sections
- Achievement screens
- XP rewards
- Streak counters
- Landing page highlights

Do not use Bebas Neue for:

- Reading pages
- Vocabulary content
- Grammar lessons
- Dashboard widgets
- Forms
- Settings pages
- Long headings

---

UI Heading Font (Outfit)

Use for:

- h1
- h2
- h3
- Dashboard titles
- Lesson titles
- Section headers
- Modal titles

This is the default heading font across the product.

---

Body Font (Inter)

Use for:

- Paragraphs
- Learning content
- Reading articles
- Vocabulary definitions
- Form labels
- Buttons
- Navigation links

Prioritize readability.

---

## Educational First Principle

This is an educational product.

When visual style conflicts with readability,
learning efficiency always wins.

Never sacrifice usability for aesthetics.

Think like an EdTech product designer,
not a game designer.

---

## Reading Experience Rules

Reading pages are the highest priority screens.

Requirements:

- Minimal distractions
- Maximum readability
- Comfortable line length
- Comfortable line spacing
- Clean typography

Avoid:

- Strong gradients
- Heavy glow effects
- Graffiti decorations
- Animated backgrounds

Reading content should feel closer to
Medium, Kindle, or Notion than a game UI.

---

## Card Style

Use glassmorphism-inspired cards.

Card style:

- subtle blur
- rounded corners
- thin neon border
- soft shadow

Avoid heavy glow effects.

---

## Buttons

Primary Buttons:

Gradient background
Neon Cyan -> Neon Purple

Hover:

- slight elevation
- soft glow
- 200ms transition

Avoid aggressive animations.

---

## Animations

Animation duration:

200ms - 300ms

Use:

- fade
- slide
- scale

Avoid:

- bounce
- shake
- flashing
- strobe effects

---

## Reading Pages

Reading pages are the most important screens.

Rules:

- maximum readability
- large line height
- clean layout
- minimal visual distractions

Do not place decorative graffiti elements
inside reading content.

---

## Vocabulary Pages

Vocabulary cards should feel modern and playful.

Allowed:

- Neon accents
- XP indicators
- Progress animations

Not allowed:

- Graffiti text styles
- Complex backgrounds

---

## Gamification

Use graffiti-inspired visuals only for:

- XP rewards
- Achievement badges
- Level up screens
- Learning streaks

Examples:

LEVEL UP
VOCAB MASTER
7 DAY STREAK

These areas may contain stronger graffiti styling.

---

## Layout Rules

Desktop:

Max content width:
1280px

Reading content:
700px - 850px

Mobile-first responsive design.

Always provide:

- generous spacing
- clean hierarchy
- clear CTA placement

---

## Accessibility

Minimum contrast ratio:
WCAG AA

Never sacrifice readability
for visual style.

All text must remain easy to read.

---

## UI Inspirations

Primary references:

- Duolingo
- Spotify
- Notion
- Linear

Avoid copying designs directly.

Use them only as inspiration.

---

## Agent Instructions

When generating UI:

1. Prioritize learning efficiency.
2. Prioritize readability.
3. Use neon accents sparingly.
4. Use graffiti elements only as highlights.
5. Keep interfaces clean and modern.
6. Think like an EdTech designer, not a game designer.
7. Every screen should feel calm, cool, and motivating.